(Lakoff, Johnson, Turner, Fauconnier), it promotes a conceptual metaphor model that allows readers to discover the innovative ways poets translate “melody,” “dynamics,” “tempo,” “mood,” and other musical elements into literal and figurative expressions that invite readers to imagine the music in their mind’s eye (i.e., their mind’s ear).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAmerican poetryxAfrican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish languagexRhythm. 0aJazz in literature. 0aJazzxHistory and criticism. 0aMusic and literature. 0aPoetryxHistory and criticism. 4aAmerikanische Literatur. 4aIntermedialität. 4aJazz-Musik. 4aKognitive Poetik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican Literature.  aCognitive Poetics.  aIntermediality.  aJazz Music.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831103952800 cprintz978311032654340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033901740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110339017423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110339017/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT 